## cols(
##   waterYear = col_integer(),

Chaco SPI and Chuska SWE

  • The percent of times swe the anomaly for the year and spi had the same sign 56.25%

  • The percent of times swe anomaly for the year was positive and was followed by a positive spi had the same sign out of all positive swe years 66.6666667%

  • The percent of times swe anomaly for the year was negative and was followed by a negative spi had the same sign out of all negative swe years 50%

  • June SPI seems to be much more correlated to winter SWE than does July SPI
  • May is the most well correlated to winter swe

  • May positive swe & positive spi / positive swe: 83.333%
  • May negative swe & negative spi / negative swe: 50%
  • May total correct: 62.5%

Chinle SPI and Chuska SWE

  • The percent of times swe anomaly for the year was positive and was followed by a positive spi had the same sign out of all positive swe years 66.6666667%

  • The percent of times swe anomaly for the year was negative and was followed by a negative spi had the same sign out of all negative swe years 70%

  • Chuska SWE is much less corelated to Chinle July 6 month SPI than it is to June 6 month
  • May had the higest correlation

  • May positive swe & positive spi / positive swe: 83.333%
  • May negative swe & negative spi / negative swe: 60%
  • May total correct: 68.75%
